title: No objects under Context in palette when scripting a data set
description: When scripting a data set, there are no objects listed under the 'Context' section in the palette, which is unexpected.
OB: When scripting a data set, no objects are displayed under the 'Context' section in the palette.
EB: When scripting a data set, I expect to see the following objects listed under the 'Context' section in the palette: 'this,' 'row,' and 'reportContext.' Additionally, there should be other objects available for other methods.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a new data set and select it.
2. Switch to the script view, choose 'onFetch,' and open the palette.
